Books on Machine Learning
Tom Mitchel. Machine Learning. McGraw-Hill Education, 1997. Classic book!

Christopher Bishop. Pattern Recognition and Machine Learning. Springer, 2007.

Kevin P. Murphy. Machine Learning: A Probabilistic Perspective. The MIT Press, 2012.

Trevor Hastie, Robert Tibshirani, Jerome Friedman. The Elements of Statistical Learning. Second Edition, Springer, 2012.

Yaser S. Abu-Mostafa, Malik Magdon-Ismail, Hsuan-Tien Lin. Learning from Data.  AMLBook, 2012.

Mehryar Mohri, Afshin Rostamizadeh, Ameet Talwalkar. Foundations of Machine Learning. MIT Press, 2012.

Peter Flach. Machine Learning: The Art and Science of Algorithms that Make Sense of Data. Cambridge university Press, 2012.

Ethem Alpaydin . Introduction to Machine Learning. MIT Press, 2014. Gareth James, Daniela Witten, Trevor Hastie, Robert Tibshirani. An Introduction to Statistical Learning: with Applications in R. Springer, 2015.

John D. Kelleher, Brian Mac Namee, Aoife D'Arcy. Fundamentals of Machine Learning for Predictive Data Analytics: Algorithms, Worked Examples, and Case Studies. MIT Press, 2015


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



Books on R
John Chambers. Software for Data Analysis: Programming with R. Springer. 2008.

Norman Matloff. The Art of R Programming. No Starch Press, 2011.

Robert Kabacoff. R in Action. Manning. 2011.

Joseph Adler. R in a Nutshell. O’Reilly. 2012. Paul Teetor. R Cookbook. O’Reilly. 2011.

J. Abedin and K. Das. Data Manipulation with R. PACKT. 2015

Donato Teutonico. Instant R Starter, PACKT. 2013.